-- Damas Says Bank Lenders Agree to Extend Debt Standstill Till January 31
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-12-28T12:14:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/damas-says-bank-lenders-agree-to-extend-debt-standstill-till-january-31.html
Damas International Ltd., a Dubai-
based jewelry maker and retailer, said its bank lenders agreed
to extend the standstill period for its banking facilities to
Jan. 31.   The company is in final negotiations with lenders on
restructuring plan over its bank facilities, Damas said in a
statement to Nasdaq Dubai today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  